ADDIN0:
Rapinoe and Sydney Leroux on Twitter. I honestly want to move to Seattle later in life as ive really fallen in love with the city through Seattle's 90+ videos and the photos from their practices etc. Seems like a very awesome place.

ADDIN1: edible team and such a talented group of young ladies. Laura Harvey being coach and GM is brilliant. I respect her very much and am very excited about this upcoming season. Currently in the process of finding a new job which very well could relocate me to
ADDIN2: a half hour's way outside of Orlando and then i'll become a HUGE Pride fan(my goal primarily is to support the NWSL) and as I haven't been within 8 hours of a team living in central Alabama(The Dash are about 9 hours away lol) I plan to support any local
ADDIN3:
NWSL team I can, but SRFC will remain number 1. Definitely will be cheering for them when they come to Orlando. 

Also thank you for this survey. I really think fan response is something the league can use to their advantage. So many of the fans are all
ADDIN4: over the world, you'd be astounded at the following this league actually has, just so many people don't even know of its existence. Very excited about its historic 5th season though and the recent news of salary increases and new locations on the horizon

to bring new teams in.

Addins: Being a poor person, I'm really price conscious of everything. I'm usually willing to sacrifice in terms of convenience or quality in exchange for a cheaper price. It's one of the reasons I'm able to afford season tickets (they are fantastically priced).
ADDIN0: The team is fantastic, and I love hearing/reading about them where I can find it. There's little of any coverage outside of dedicated twitter or reddit feeds (shout out to reign subreddit). Harvey is wonderful, Solo is/was wonderful, Pinoe is wonderful.
ADDIN1:
I'm a bit sad about Kim, who isn't, but I still love the team. 

Last year, the ceremony/celebration around Pride and the Orlando shooting was incredibly meaningful as someone in the GLBT community. It's so great and refreshing to see that kind of suppor
ADDIN2:
t in a sports franchise. It meant a lot to me, so Thank You. 

My main complaints are around the league being less than transparent. The whole field issue with WNY Flash that cost us that game, and then they beat us into the playoffs by the same amount of
ADDIN3:
points? That's bullshit to me. I'd rather we delayed a match than risk playing on some crappy field because NWSL doesn't have it's shit together. 

Everyone I've brought to a game though, has loved the experience. I find it a great environment, outside t
ADDIN4: he notorious Memorial Field bathrooms. In a consumer experience, that's the real downside issue. I'd love to see the Reign buy the stadium (we can dream right?) and renovate the whole thing. The size is fantastic, it just needs some grass and a facilities
ADDIN5:
overhaul to be a fantastic venue. 

The merch that I have bought has been amazing. Sadly, I tend to lose things, and lost a Reign hoodie last year that I loved. Oh, the woes of being poor. Anyway, thank you for being a fantastic organization and a fantas
ADDIN6:
tic club. 

My one last suggestion is maybe, if possible, teaming up with the sounders to leverage their marketing/merch teams? There has to be some way to use their existing network to facilitate things with Reign

ADDIN0: y of the field (turf, size, football lines, etc.) is not befitting a professional women's team.  For that reason alone, I believe the Reign deserves to play at Centurylink Stadium.  I would even brave the traffic and endure (unhappily) the $30 parking fee
ADDIN1: to attend, but I do hope that perhaps the price for parking could be lowered.  I would be concerned about the attendance, though.  I am sad when Memorial Stadium isn't full, and I think it would be even more obvious in such a gigantic stadium like Centur
ADDIN2: ylink.  In the end, I love these ladies and I will be there to support them, no matter where they play!  I also am a fan of how the Reign is run administratively, especially compared to Western NY Flash.  Thank you for supporting Megan Rapinoe, Hope Solo,
ADDIN3: and for maintaining a standard of class in the NWSL.  Go Reign!!!

Addins: I think the Reign did very well handling stories about both Hope Solo and Megan Rapinoe. The contrast with the Washington Spirit was striking. In general, I appreciate that the Reign seems to be supportive of its players. That's really important, especial
ADDIN0: ly when no one is making much money. Being decent to your players doesn't affect the salary cap. With current events being what they are, I think we may see more athletes speaking up about important issues that are bigger than sports in the near future. I
ADDIN1:
hope we do. 

I really like going to games at Memorial. Starfire is too small, too far away, and too hard to get to. CenturyLink Field is obviously much too large at this time, although it would be cool to see a Reign/Sounders doubleheader someday. 

Tha
ADDIN2:
nks for letting me lock my bike to the fence inside the stadium! It seems much more secure there than at the racks outside the stadium.

At some point it might make sense to have a second merchandize stand on the other side of the stadium. 

The only thin
ADDIN3: g I really miss about Starfire is the opportunity to drink a beer while watching the game. I wish we could do that at Memorial. But I've heard people walking by outside the beer garden fence ask people inside what event is going on, and learning about the
ADDIN4:
Reign for the first time that way. That's cool to see. Adding some standing-height tables in the beer garden would be much appreciated.

Laura Harvey is a treasure. Aside from the fact that she's a great coach, I think it's cool that the Reign actually h
ADDIN5:
ave a woman coaching their team. It's too bad there's not more female coaches in the league.

I didn't make it to the season ticket holder event this year, but I had a great time at the event in 2015. It was really cool to see part of a team training. If
ADDIN6:
you do another season ticket holder event in 2017, I'd prefer an event on a training day rather than a game day if possible.

Addins: After a rocky first season, I feel like SRFC made a real commitment to improving the team and the overall fan experience, and it shows. Memorial Stadium has some real problems, but I don't know that there are superior options. The bathrooms are terrible,
ADDIN0: yes, and it feels silly to have a beer garden without a view of the game. In these two areas, Starfire was superior, but I think Memorial's problems are outweighed by the value of having matches in Seattle proper. The concessions could certainly be better
ADDIN1:
too, as could the merch area. I've only tried buying SRFC merch at a match a couple of times, mostly just because the merch area feels a bit crammed and chaotic. Feels much more pleasant to buy online. 

Oh! And also, Memorial has an *unbelievably* bad P
ADDIN2:
A system!

It is my impression that players like to be a part of this organization and feel well-treated, and that's important to me as a fan of the team. 

I enjoy how easy it is to get into Reign matches as compared to entering CenturyLink. I do think i
ADDIN3: t's time for proper bike parking. I am glad that staff are understanding about the need to lock bikes somewhere, and so far, I've never had any trouble locking my bike to the fence as instructed by staff. But more and more people are biking, and I think t
ADDIN4:
hat space will soon be insufficient. 

Please keep Laura Harvey around forever!

Addins: Overall, we really enjoy the convenience and experience of attending the games and of being fans.  Our young daughters are soccer players and you cannot underestimate the impact of the players as role models and examples of what one can achieve.  My girls
ADDIN0: will never grow up to be Marshawn Lynch or Clint Dempsey, but they might grow up to be Megan Rapinoe, Jessica Fishlock, or Kim Little.  You've given them something tangible to witness and strive for.  Plus, I want them out there cheering on a regular bas
ADDIN1: is for tough women who are kicking ass without apology.  We appreciate the access to the players and the graciousness with which they conduct themselves while signing autographs and while on the bench.  We've even been lucky enough to have Haley Kopmeyer
ADDIN2:
and Merritt Mathias guest coach our girls at their Highline Select practices and that has been HUGE to solidify our loyalty to the Reign.

While I don't pretend to understand what goes on behind the scenes, I would support any and all efforts to promote t
ADDIN3: he Reign (and women's soccer overall) more aggressively in the community.  I'd like to see packages that incentivize entire youth teams or clubs to attend en masse, some cross marketing to engage the enormous fan base of the Sounders FC, and more publicit
ADDIN4: y when marquee players come to town to drive interest.  The women's movement is strong and growing right now and I'd like to see Women's Soccer capitalize on the notion that supporting these players, this team, and this league is a tangible way to vote wi
ADDIN5: th your dollars to put strong women front and center and have a great time doing so.

ADDIN1: apinoe's gesture. I was less appreciative of the lawsuit by women players seeking more money. If you can get more dough from sponsors, TV, tickets and merchandise, I think that would be awesome. But you can't pay higher salaries until you have the money.

ADDIN1: philosophies and team economics in the NWSL.  In other words, when WoSo takes itself seriously as a sport.  The British contingent at the Reign seem to bring that focus, and I hope that the USWNT hype machine will start promoting the sport itself, instea
ADDIN2: d of just pushing replica shirt sales at endless, meaningless exhibition games.

Addins: We attend matches to support quality, high level women soccer i.e. see the beautiful game in person.  This season, the environment has turned more activist, non-family friendly and the game is more like a sideshow to a carnival.  One of my family members
ADDIN0: is a veteran.  I do not want to attend a match and see Rapinoe's take a knee.  I don't care about the players' sexual orientation, I want to see and support good soccer and have players play with skill, intensity, passion, and smarts.  Sadly, half of my f
ADDIN1:
amily no longer wants to attend games because they feel it is validating Rapinoe's stance.

I also don't like the Reign partnering with one youth club Seattle United.  The Reign financially benefit from the pay to play Seattle United youth club system and
ADDIN2: this is driving up the youth club cost for all players.  While financial viability is very important for the Reign, I am not sure if the underpaid players are reaping the majority of the benefit or if the majority is going to pay coaches, trainers, overh
ADDIN3: ead.  While Memorial Stadium is quaint, there should be a formal partnership with Seattle Sounders Men where games are played at CLink.  Those NWSL teams with that partnership will be much stronger overall and have broader support in the soccer community.

Addins:
I don't know why you devoted a section to personal values. It really had no place in this survey.
I think Reign FC website's focus on selling gear - in the past anyway-  was way too high.  I know this is a way of bringing in revenue and that revenue is im
ADDIN0: portant, especially since women's sports don't have the same support as men's sports. But, I also think you should focus on a website that has more information about your players. I like to read about player backgrounds and prior experience, or what they
ADDIN1: are doing in the community, etc.  As for Megan Rapinoe taking a knee, I was proud of her, and proud of Laura Harvey and the team for giving her their support.  As for Hope Solo, she is an amazing player and I used to think of her as a great role model for
ADDIN2: women and young girls. But I think her careless public comments and personal issues -involvement with violence (both by her and against her by her H) have really detracted from that important role.  I know male athletes are not judged so harshly for thei
ADDIN3: r personal flaws, but sadly, that is the world we live in at this moment. So, if it is known that players have issues - such as DV involvement, substance abuse, etc. - the administration does to be proactive and offer education and training, etc.  to get
ADDIN4: ahead of these issues to avoid these personal issues from spilling into their professional positions.

Addins: 1. The question about my experience of retail purchasing had two parts.  One the left, it asked for my experience, on the right it asked me to rank the importance of it to me (I think).  This was an identical format to the previous page, but for this set
ADDIN0: of questions I could not access the answers on the right side of the page -- that is, I could only see the "not at all important" and the next set of response buttons, but nothing at the upper end of the scale.  And it would not let me proceed without ans
ADDIN1:
wering, so I ended up marking them all on the second set of response buttons, but I would not consider these valid responses.
2. While it seems as though, based on my family income, that Reign games and merchandise should not seem expensive to me, after p
ADDIN2: aying my daughter's soccer fees, tournament costs, school tuition, etc. and my own student loans, mortgage etc., we really don't have a lot of disposable income.  So while I don't come to games as often as I'd like to, we do it as often as we can fit it i
ADDIN3: nto my budget and my daughter's soccer schedule.  I'd love more affordable merchandise, but in all honesty, there will probably always be other priorities.  I love the Reign and wish I could support you more with attendance, purchases, etc.  I do have a b
ADDIN4:
ig Reign sticker on the back of my car, though. :-)
3. I probably attend more S2 games than either Sounders or Reign games.  The main reasons are affordability and that I happen to work on Fort Dent Way, so the games are very convenient for me.  The other
ADDIN5: thing I love about Starfire Stadium is how close we are to the players and the game.  Makes the game so much more exciting.  I do look forward to the day that the Reign fills Century Link stadium with cheering fans.
